java.lang.Object

Base class for transponder.

readMultipleBlocks

public int readMultipleBlocks(int firstDataBlock,
                              int noOfDataBlocks,
                              FedmIscTagHandler_Result result)
                       throws FePortDriverException,
                              FeReaderDriverException,
                              FedmException
Read of transponder data

Parameters:
firstDataBlock - first data block address
noOfDataBlocks - number of requested data blocks
result - FedmIscTagHandler_Result object containing return values
Returns:
operation status

Description:
Basic [0xB0][0x23] Read Multiple Blocks command
- Without support for extended address mode
- Without request of security status
The return value status indicates the success:
0 - tramsmission was successful
status byte (>1), if the reader signals a problem
error code (<0), if something goes wrong
The result object of type FedmIscTagHandler_Result contains only valid data (result.blockSize and result.data), if the operation status is 0.

Throws:
FedmException
FePortDriverException
FeReaderDriverException

public int readMultipleBlocksWithSecStatus(int firstDataBlock,
                                           int noOfDataBlocks,
                                           FedmIscTagHandler_Result result)
                                    throws FePortDriverException,
                                           FeReaderDriverException,
                                           FedmException
Read of transponder data with additional security status

Parameters:
firstDataBlock - first data block address
noOfDataBlocks - number of requested data blocks
result - FedmIscTagHandler_Result object containing return values
Returns:
operation status

Description:
Basic [0xB0][0x23] Read Multiple Blocks command with additional security status
- Without support for extended address mode

The return value status indicates the success:
0 - tramsmission was successful
status byte (>1), if the reader signals a problem
error code (<0), if something goes wrong
The result object of type FedmIscTagHandler_Result contains only valid data (result.blockSize, result.data and result.securityStatus), if the operation status is 0.

Throws:
FedmException
FePortDriverException
FeReaderDriverException

writeMultipleBlocks

public int writeMultipleBlocks(int firstDataBlock,
                               int noOfDataBlocks,
                               int blockSize,
                               byte[] data)
                        throws FePortDriverException,
                               FeReaderDriverException,
                               FedmException
Write of transponder data

Parameters:
firstDataBlock - first data block address
noOfDataBlocks - number of requested data blocks
blockSize - number of bytes in each data block
data - byte array with transponder data to be written to
Returns:
operation status

Description:
Basic [0xB0][0x24] Write Multiple Blocks command
- Without support for extended address mode

The return value status indicates the success:
0 - tramsmission was successful
status byte (>1), if the reader signals a problem
error code (<0), if something goes wrong

If the return status is 0x03, the errorDBAddress is set.

Throws:
FedmException
FePortDriverException
FeReaderDriverException
